title: Bindaas
subTitle: Abhi falls in love with Kajol and convinces her family to get them married. However, things get complicated when Kajol's uncle asks him to kill their rival's son, who is none other than Abhi himself.

title: Katmundu
subTitle: Three friends, Sidhu, Sunny and Pablo, decide to go to Nepal on a holiday. However, their happiness is ruined by two girls, Pallabi and Rai.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: Lord Shiva loses his temper when Kambasura comes to take Parvati with him, and Parvati accepts Narada's advice to win Lord Shiva's heart.

title: Fight 1:1
subTitle: Two rival groups compete against each other in all aspects of their college life. However, the only obstruction to their growing enmity is their extremely disciplined dean.

title: Kali Sankar
subTitle: Three children are separated due to circumstances following their father's murder. Later, after the eldest returns home from prison, his grandfather urges him to seek vengeance for his father's death.

title: Mahaan
subTitle: Ajit adopts Chandu, who later falls for a girl named Mala. Trouble arises for Chandu when Mala's father turns out to be Ajit's boss.

title: Nater Guru
subTitle: A terrible heart attack leaves Sulochana in a vulnerable position. To ease her burdens, Sulochana's daughter reaches out to her estranged husband for help.

title: Bidroho
subTitle: Uttam's ailing mother dies after not getting proper treatment when the landlord refuses to help them. Later, he decides to exact revenge against the injustice done to him.

title: Chhoto Bou
subTitle: A mother-in-law treats her daughters-in-law, Mamta, Tandra and Deepa, according to their husband's income. However, when she falls ill, she realises her folly.

title: Dui Prithibi
subTitle: Raised by his widowed mother, Tonmoy is a collegian in love with Moina. He loses his memory after a violent altercation and is taken to his father's friend's house where he falls in love with Farah.

title: Dui Prithibi
subTitle: Raised by his widowed mother, Tonmoy is a collegian in love with Moina. He loses his memory after a violent altercation and is taken to his father's friend's house where he falls in love with Farah.

title: Ami Je Tomari
subTitle: When Amar and Jyoti's relationship is not accepted by their family members, they elope. All hell breaks loose when Ajit, who was supposed to marry Jyoti, tries to harm the couple.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: As Parvati attempts to make a Shivling, Lord Shiva destroys it and seeks to prevent her from doing it. However, she refuses to give up and continues to battle the challenges he throws her. Will she succeed?

title: Amar Kantak
subTitle: Binu relocates for a job, but soon afterwards, he loses contact with his family. His brother, Debesh, strives to look for him, but he stumbles upon some disturbing clues.

title: Bhai Amar Bhai
subTitle: Three children lose their father and get separated from each other while escaping a fire. However, when they reunite, they vow to take revenge against their father's killer.

title: Indrajit
subTitle: Indrajit is an honest police officer who punishes Raja, an MLA's son, for raping a girl. The MLA then kidnaps the former's son and demands Raja's release.

title: Dujone
subTitle: Akash is the son of a rich industrialist who falls in love with a poor girl and intends to marry her. Soon, their families find out and start opposing their relationship.

title: Chirodini Tumi Je Amar
subTitle: Pallavi, a rich, spoilt girl, falls in love with Krishna, a scooter mechanic, and gets married without her parents' approval. The situation takes an ugly turn when her family tries to separate them.

title: Yuddha
subTitle: Agnishwar Rai, a noble officer, is stone-hearted towards criminals and gets arrested when he puts an MLA behind bars. Filled with anger, he avenges his wife's death, after she was murdered by the same bureaucrat.

title: Phirie Dao
subTitle: When an unfortunate circumstance gets a child's father killed and mother paralysed by dacoits, he grows up learning martial arts to get revenge on those who turned his life upside down.

title: Phirie Dao
subTitle: When an unfortunate circumstance gets a child's father killed and mother paralysed by dacoits, he grows up learning martial arts to get revenge on those who turned his life upside down.

title: Apur Panchali
subTitle: Arko, a film student, invites Subir, who played the legendary role of Apu, to attend an award ceremony in Germany. But the old man hesitates to accept the invitation.

title: Shiv Shakti
subTitle: Making Parvati's path more difficult, Lord Shiva disguises himself as a saint and distracts her. However, Parvati is determined to complete her purpose.

title: Monchuri
subTitle: Two friends enter an institution to become the most successful career thieves. Eventually, they befriend a man who desires to become a minister through the art of thievery.

title: Janmadata
subTitle: A pair of close friends turn into enemies. Their grandchildren resolve to bring their families back together.

title: Pratarak
subTitle: A young man leaves his wealthy father to work in the city without knowing of a conspiracy by a trusted manager to take over his parent's business.

title: Fighter, Marbo Noy Morbo
subTitle: Surya, a college student, decides to exact revenge on a local gangster after he frames and kills his elder brother, ACP Bose.

title: Subho Drishti
subTitle: Bringing the best in cinema.

title: I Love You
subTitle: Santosh, a carefree youth, parts ways with his lover, Dharmika, during his college days. Years later, after his marriage to Gowri, he runs into her, which leaves him in a dilemma.

title: Shotru
subTitle: Sub-inspector Dibakar Singho settles every dispute in his town with wisdom and logic. However, he is compelled to use force when an extortionist with mafia links - Arjun Sarkar - confronts him.
